Key Match Events: Donovan Mitchell scored a game-winning jumper with three-tenths of a second left
Damian Lillard had 41 points with nine assists and shot 10 of 15 from 3-point range
Pre-Game Insights: The Cavaliers were missing Caris LeVert due to a sore right knee
The Bucks played without Khris Middleton, who hasn't yet made his season debut as he recovers from surgery on his ankles
Post-Match Reflections: The Cavaliers remained unbeaten with a 114-113 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks
Milwaukee has lost five straight since winning its opener
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cavaliers are one win away from matching their best start in franchise history
They won their first eight games in 1976-77
The Bucks need more from Gary Trent Jr., who scored three points in 34 minutes
Others: Giannis Antetokounmpo had 34 points, 16 rebounds and nine assists for the Bucks
The teams meet again Monday in Cleveland
